10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. DeepL is best suited for businesses, translators, content teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Smartling, meanwhile, shines for enterprise localization, SaaS companies, global brands, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, DeepL describes itself as \"AI-powered translation tool renowned for natural and accurate translations.\" Smartling, established in 2009, positions itself as \"Enterprise translation management platform combining AI and human translation.\" With 8 years between them, Smartling brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while DeepL offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **DeepL** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 8.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Smartling is a poor choice — far from it. Smartling excels in its own right, particularly for enterprise localization and SaaS companies.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best translation quality for european languages, go with DeepL. If excellent enterprise tms platform matters more to you, Smartling is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
